A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Mr. Francis Malan Yao; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Mr. Francis Malan Yao on February 9, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Mr. Francis Malan Yao was born on April 8, 1945, in Assinie-Mafia, Cote
5 d'Ivoire; and
6 WHEREAS, from 1977 to 2000, Mr. Francis Malan Yao served with the United States
7 Embassy in Cote d'Ivoire, where he served as a Monitor Extraordinaire and Shift Supervisor
8 at the United States Foreign Broadcasting Information Service (FBIS); and
9 WHEREAS, as one of the founding members of the FBIS in Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire, he
10 played a pivotal role in overseeing personnel and assets, as well as coordinating United
11 States Embassy's bureau coverage of significant regional events across Africa, including
12 wars, coups, and natural disasters; and
13 WHEREAS, in 2002, Mr. Francis Malan Yao moved to the United States, where his
14 expertise and commitment were instrumental in training monitors in new FBIS bureaus
