15 across various countries, further solidifying his reputation as a respected leader and mentor;
16 and
17 WHEREAS, in 2008, Mr. Francis Malan Yao settled in Atlanta, Georgia, where he became
18 an active and cherished member of the diaspora community; and
19 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife, and was blessed with eight
20 remarkable children who carry forward his legacy of service, integrity, and community
21 engagement; and
22 WHEREAS, he gave inspiration to many through his high ideals, morals, and deep concern
23 for his fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding he demonstrated to his
24 family and friends were admired by others; and
25 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
26 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
27 made this world a better place in which to live; and
28 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Mr. Francis Malan Yao will long be
29 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
30 had the great fortune of knowing him.
31 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
32 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Mr. Francis Malan Yao
33 and express their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
